The paper introduces a deep reinforcement learning library that implements a comprehensive set of DRL algorithms and techniques drawn from the state-of-the-art research in the field. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the library is designed for robotics applications, which suggests that it may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Lastly, the paper mentions a visualization tool for the qualitative inspection of trained agents, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
